INSERT INTO cmorvar VALUES('es-MIP_LPday','day','land','water_evaporation_flux_from_soil','kg m-2 s-1','area: mean where land time: mean','area: areacella','Bare Soil Evaporation','Water here means water in all phases. Evaporation is the conversion of liquid or solid into vapor. (The conversion of solid alone into vapor is called ''sublimation''.) In accordance with common usage in geophysical disciplines, ''flux'' implies per unit area, called ''flux density'' in physics.','longitude latitude time','es','real','','','','','','','');
INSERT INTO cmorvar VALUES('esn-MIP_LPday','day','land','water_evapotranspiration_flux','kg m-2 s-1','area: mean where land time: mean','area: areacella','Snow Evaporation','Water here means water in all phases. Evaporation is the conversion of liquid or solid into vapor. (The conversion of solid alone into vapor is called ''sublimation''.) In accordance with common usage in geophysical disciplines, ''flux'' implies per unit area, called ''flux density'' in physics. Unless indicated in the cell_methods attribute, a quantity is assumed to apply to the whole area of each horizontal grid box. Previously, the qualifier where_type was used to specify that the quantity applies only to the part of the grid box of the named type.  Names containing the where_type qualifier are deprecated and newly created data should use the cell_methods attribute to indicate the horizontal area to which the quantity applies.','longitude latitude time','esn','real','','','','','','','');
